      h1.content-heading.content-heading--v-even Mini Autobiography
      p.
        Ever since an early age, I have been heavily invested in computers and electronics. I played a TON of video games as a kid and I still do to this day. Sometime around grade eight
        I thought it would be cool to make a video game of my own, so I did! It was awful but I really enjoyed making it and I discovered my love for development and programming. I knew early on
        in high school that I wanted to pursue a career in software engineering so that's what I did. The University of Waterloo looked like it was full of tremendous opportunities, so I figured
        I belonged there. Waterloo is of close proximity to my home town too, so that's where I set my sights. I have always excelled in school so I was accepted into the Software Engineering
        program without too much trouble. Since then, I have continued to shine in my studies. I have had four internships to date, all of which have been terrific. Two of them were
        at Sony based in Waterloo where I worked on both Media Go and the PlayStation Web Store. The third was at Yelp in San Francisco working with the Internationalization team on cool
        experiment stuff related to their sign up page. I secured a position at Google in New York for my most recent coop job, did a bunch of stuff for knowledge panels on Search and now
        I'm back in Waterloo. Overall, I'm killing it and I'm very happy to be where I am (end humble brag).
