      h1.content-heading.content-heading--v-even Hobbies and Interests
      p.
        Previously I stated that I play an exceptional amount of video games, but I also have other interests too. Somewhat recently, I have fell in love with juggling. At my first internship
        with Sony, compile times were kind of long so I found myself wanting to do something during those times. Some of my co-workers were juggling veterans so I picked it up myself. I'm still
        quite the amateur but I know a few 3-ball patterns and two 4-ball patterns. Another one of my hobbies is volleyball. I'm about 6'4" so I'm well suited for the sport and my favourite position
        is middle. I was captain of my school's volleyball team in grade twelve and I played on a rep volleyball team during my last three years of high school. My team travelled all around Ontario
        to compete. Nowadays I just play the sport casually when I get the chance. In high school, my classes weren't very compelling, so I became an origami connoisseur to help fill my time. I
        focused a lot on modular origami (origami where models are built out of several of the exact same piece) due to its heavy connections with geometry. Board games and card games are also things
        I have a passion for. I played tons of Magic: The Gathering during the Return to Ravnica block and won a few #[a(href='http://archive.wizards.com/Magic/tcg/events.aspx?x=events/magic/fnm') FNMs]
        at my local game store but me (and my wallet) have taken a break from the activity, for now. I also like the board games #[a(href='https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dominion_(card_game)') Dominion]
        and #[a(href='http://www.catan.com/') Settlers of Catan]. Lastly, I play a little bit of the guitar, and although I enjoy it, I'm pretty bad.
